column2: Fine particles suspended in water.  Looks like pollen.
No suspended particles in water as there was on last test date 8/17/94.
Minor debris floating in water caused by high windy conditions 9/7/94.
Lake level up 6" in one week.  Recent heavy rains caused dirty run-off from new construction on north side of lake - into swamp that has a channel to the lake - 4 boats sunk tied to dock.
Cloudy + overcast - heavy rain all day 9/22/94.
Windy until about 2:00 p.m. - took reading at different location on north shore.
Last reading for 1994.  Lake calm for 2 days - no appreciable wind.
Slight overcast 58 degrees.  Ice out 4/17/95.  Water is cold - no swimming.
High thin clouds-algae starting to form in other parts of the lake-people swimming and fishing.
Aspen pollen floating on water- air temp. 55 degrees.
Lake calm-bits of algae just below surface-air temp. 78 degrees.
Suspended particles in water-lake calm-85 degrees-after swimming eyes itch.
Big boats on lake 6-25-95.  Operating fairly close to shore disturbing lake bottom with big waves.
Very few boats on lake since 7-4-95.  Bottom has settled down.
Algae or pollen suspended in lake- very hot 97 degrees.
No big boats on lake since 7-16-95.
With all the hot weather and lack of rain lake level has dropped 18" from high water mark!!
Calm-no breeze-not a ripple in the water.
Very windy-choppy waters-45 degrees-last reading for '95-boat out of water.
Partly cloudy and windy.  Warm- 86 degrees.
Very nice day.  Calm and sunny.
Calm and sunny day.  No boats.
Clear and sunny day.  No boats.
Sunny- cool water.  Cloudy.  No boats.
Calm- hazy- no boats- clear water
Cloudy- heavy rains on 7/8- lake up 4"- no boats- water cloudy.
Clear.  Rain 8/1/01.  Lake a little low.  Boat and jet ski traffic.
Clear day- some jet skis- heavy rain 8/12/01.
Rain yesterday.  Nice day today.  No boat traffic.
Sunny- no speed boats.  Three fisherman.  Calm waters.
Sunny- nice day- and calm waters.
Sunny.  Many boats and jet skis over the weekend.
Sunny- nice- clear day.  Jet ski and large power boat traffic the day before.
Junk floating in water- sunny- clear day- no boat traffic- and small waves.
Clear day- calm waters- and no boat traffic.
Clear sunny day.  No boat traffic.  Holiday pretty hectic. A lot of floating junk.
Partly sunny. A lot of rain lately.
Partly cloudy- slight wind from the east.  A lot of rain lately.
warm clear sunny day- few boats
nice clear- sunny day- no boats- no wind
clear skies- heavy boat traffic last few days
Clear sunny day.  Light boat traffic.
Sunny day.  No boat traffic.  Wind 15 mph.  Lake down about 2' from normal.
Partly cloudy- slightly wavy- lake level at highest ever- power boat wakes washing more dirt in.
Mostly cloudy- slightly wavy- minimal boat traffic- air temp 80 degree F
partly cloudy- warm-83 degrees F- slightly wavy
Partly cloudy- wavy- some big waves from boat wakes- lost temp readings but they were similar to 07/12/2017.
Sunny- windy- wavy- lake turning over; not much difference in temperature readings
